## THREADED PIPELINE ARCHITECTURE

Every engagement runs as a set of parallel threads. Each thread owns its own
directory, log file, and structured output. The parent agent monitors all threads
and synthesizes results. No finding advances without thread evidence.

### Directory Structure
```
/tmp/scout/sessions/<session-id>/
  threads/
    thread-01-recon/
      cmd.log          # every command with timestamp
      raw/             # verbatim tool output files
      report.json      # structured thread output
    thread-02-web2/
      cmd.log
      raw/
      report.json
    thread-03-web3/
      cmd.log
      raw/
      report.json
    thread-04-mobile/  # for iOS/Android targets
      cmd.log
      raw/
      report.json
  triage/
    candidates.json    # all candidates from all threads
    confirmed.json     # survived all gates
    killed.json        # KILL verdicts with reason
  report.md
  session.json         # active target, scope, thread status
```

### Thread Lifecycle
1. **Spawn**: create `threads/thread-NN-<type>/` directory
2. **Log**: every command written to `cmd.log` with timestamp before execution
3. **Capture**: raw tool output saved verbatim to `raw/<toolname>-<timestamp>.txt`
4. **Report**: structured JSON written to `report.json` when thread completes
5. **Pipe**: parent reads `report.json` from each thread into triage

### Thread Report Schema (report.json)
```json
{
  "thread_id": "thread-01-recon",
  "type": "recon|web2|web3|mobile|re",
  "target": "<surface>",
  "status": "running|complete|error",
  "candidates": [
    {
      "id": "<sha256 of title+location>",
      "title": "<finding title>",
      "class": "<vuln class>",
      "location": "<file:line or url or contract:function:line>",
      "raw_evidence": "<path to raw output file>",
      "status": "THEORETICAL|LIKELY|CONFIRMED",
      "kill_check": "<null or KILL PATTERN N — reason>"
    }
  ],
  "errors": [],
  "commands_run": N
}
```

### Full Detail Harvester Protocol
Every piece of raw output is preserved. Nothing is summarized away at thread level.
Parent synthesizes; threads only collect.

For each tool execution:
```bash
# Log the command
echo "[$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)] CMD: $cmd" >> threads/thread-NN/cmd.log

# Run and capture
$cmd 2>&1 | tee threads/thread-NN/raw/<tool>-$(date +%s).txt

# Never discard raw output
```

